text.tspan: Daily new estimated infections of COVID-19, United States
Mean estimates from epidemiological models of the true number of infections. Estimates differ because the
models differ in data used and assumptions made. Confirmed cases—which are infections that have been
confirmed with a test—are shown for comparison.
Data source: Imperial College London (2022) and other sources
Note: This chart shows the latest available model estimates as of 6 July 2023. As of this date, all models have stopped releasing updates.
The uncertainty range for each estimate — which can be large — is not shown here but can be found in the individual model charts.
